LINK INFO:

hey @Josiah @Zane Brzezinski
Every CTA in the ad i.e. every answer should be tagged with a unique link.
Sample link is as follows -
saavn://trigger_event?referrer=ad_project=rich_user_data&screen_name=home&ad_variant=marital_status_01&ad_type=in_feed&sec_pos=row1&cat_id=campaign_01&sec_id=marital_status&sec_title=Are_you_married&entity_id=yes&entity_name=Oh,Yes!&entity_type=button&sec_type=single_choice
Within this link, we will need to tweak the values of few params depending on the scenario.
Except following params, you can leave rest of the values constant as it is in the above link for now.
ad_variant will be the name of the ad file. For example if we have two different variants for age bracket then we can name them age_bracket_01 and so on
ad_type will be showcase, maximus, etc as applicable
sec_id and entity_id values will be depending on the question and answer. You can find values for the same from this link - https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1TVaUxT0JMCE__CYGQW5OK4pTTvDOyV3oM_hNYNiBjWc/edit?pli=1#gid=190427656
sec_title and entity_name are basically question and answer in words respectively
sec_type can be either single_choice or multiple_choice or “date_picker” or “free field”
Please let me know if any clarification required on this. We can do a short call also or I can implement this for couple of ads and share the sample links if you want. (edited)









/// LINK GUIDE

saavn://trigger_event?referrer=
ad_project=rich_user_data&                  ##              never touch
screen_name=home&                           ##              never touch
ad_variant=marital_status_01&               ## name of ad
ad_type=in_feed&                            ## maximus or showcase
sec_pos=row1&                               ##              never touch
cat_id=campaign_01&                         ##              never touch
sec_id=marital_status&                      ## unique question type
sec_title=Are_you_married&                  ## question
entity_id=yes&                              ## answer id                    same as entity_name for
entity_name=Oh,Yes!&                        ## copy displayed to user
entity_type=button&                         ##              never touch
sec_type=single_choice&                     ## single / multiple / date / text
cluster_id=demographics_01                  ## consult sheet




//  Template version

saavn://trigger_event?referrer=
ad_project=rich_user_data&
screen_name=home&
ad_variant=marital_status_01&
ad_type=in_feed&
sec_pos=row1&
cat_id=campaign_01&
sec_id=marital_status&
sec_title=Are_you_married&
entity_id=yes&
entity_name=Oh,Yes!&
entity_type=button&
sec_type=single_choice&
cluster_id=demographics_01

